Definition : -

stack is a data structure that stores items/objects in a LAST_IN_FIRST_OUT (LIFO) manner

stack operations : -

create
push : - used to insert an element  at the top
pop  : - used to remove an element from the top
peek : - used to view the top element from the stack
isEmpty : - it checks stack is empty or not
isFull : -  while using arrays it is useful this method checks stack is empty or not
deleteStack : - it deletes entire stack from the memory



Stack creation :  array vs linkedList

with arrays it is easy to implimentation but size limitation is there for arrays


